    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is not a `new-state-mgmt` memory issue, the new state mgmt issue only persists post initial sync when a node is receiving valid aggregated/unaggregated attestations because of the state copies for verifying those attestations.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is a diff issue as we can see from the log the node runs out of memory in slot 400\r\n```\r\n[2020-04-20 15:29:17]  INFO initial-sync: Processing block 449/19046 - estimated time remaining 35m49s blocksPerSecond=8.7 peers=3\r\nfatal error: runtime: out of memory\r\n \r\nruntime stack:\r\nruntime.throw(0x1738bcf, 0x16)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/panic.go:1112 +0x72\r\nruntime.sysMap(0xc034000000, 0x4000000, 0x27af3f8)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/mem_linux.go:169 +0xc5\r\nruntime.(*mheap).sysAlloc(0x27967a0, 0x400000, 0x263d020, 0x0)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/malloc.go:715 +0x1cd\r\nruntime.(*mheap).grow(0x27967a0, 0x1, 0x0)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/mheap.go:1286 +0x11c\r\nruntime.(*mheap).allocSpan(0x27967a0, 0x1, 0x1200, 0x27af408, 0x7ff8889a9ec8)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/mheap.go:1124 +0x6a0\r\nruntime.(*mheap).alloc.func1()\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/mheap.go:871 +0x64\r\nruntime.systemstack(0x0)\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:370 +0x66\r\nruntime.mstart()\r\n    GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1041\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith that said, I'm not aware of any reporting of this today",
